WEBVTT

00:01.027 --> 00:03.028
I need your help to arrange a loan.

00:03.062 --> 00:04.382
There's the house for collateral.

00:04.383 --> 00:06.097
- You don't own the house.
- My son does.

00:06.131 --> 00:10.001
Before anything else, the process
of having him declared dead...

00:10.036 --> 00:11.703
He's prone to long disappearances.

00:11.737 --> 00:13.571
<i>We've been through this, Gillian.</i>

00:13.605 --> 00:15.940
If I could just leave some of these here.

00:19.178 --> 00:20.779
Why don't we just...

00:20.813 --> 00:22.581
Why don't we discuss this later?

00:22.615 --> 00:23.848
There's no need.

00:26.586 --> 00:28.654
When your father left his jacket

00:28.689 --> 00:30.256
this fell out of the pocket.

00:30.290 --> 00:33.058
This was my brother's.
He died in the Argonne.

00:33.093 --> 00:34.759
My father can't forgive that.

00:34.794 --> 00:36.554
I tried to stop them.
They wouldn't listen.

00:36.555 --> 00:39.697
<i>'Cause they were under orders</i>
<i>to get you what you paid for.</i>

00:39.732 --> 00:41.199
Thanks for your input.

00:41.233 --> 00:43.201
How long have you
known Mr. Rosetti?

00:43.236 --> 00:44.470
He kicks up to Joe Masseria.

00:44.504 --> 00:47.840
With whom I have a very delicate truce.

00:47.874 --> 00:50.076
<i>What might solve a problem for you,</i>

00:50.110 --> 00:53.079
<i>creates a bigger one for me.</i>

00:53.113 --> 00:55.348
- What's your name?
- Roger.

00:55.382 --> 00:57.717
You remind me of someone.

00:57.751 --> 00:59.685
I'm gonna call you James.

00:59.719 --> 01:01.954
- Why James?
- He was a king.

01:01.988 --> 01:04.089
- Good night.
- Wait.

01:04.123 --> 01:06.157
I don't think it's wise.

01:06.191 --> 01:08.325
Don't we both know how to keep a secret?

